CREATE clause:
  A relational database consists of a multiple related tables.A table consists of multiple rows and columns.CREATE STATEMENT is used to create a new table.

Syntax:
  CREATE TABLE table_name( column1 datatype(length), column2 datatype(length), column3 datatype(length),.......columnn datatype(length) PRIMARY KEY(COLUMN1, COLUMN2 ));

Example:
  CREATE TABLE department( id serial PRIMARY KEY, department_name CHARACTER VARYING (50) );
  

  
  
